1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,600
This bitch betrayed me.

2
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:29,280
Come work for me. And you'll be
in charge of all his businesses.

3
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,680
<i>Why do you still love him?</i>

4
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:33,280
Tell me. Why, Pin? Pin!

5
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:35,560
Mr. Na.

6
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,200
- Dad?
- I saw his face.

7
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,640
Who was he?

8
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,880
Yai.

9
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,680
Chief. Who's that? What happened?

10
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:58,680
I don't know him either.

11
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,800
I was just about to take him
to the hospital.

12
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:04,360
- Mr. Tong?
- Mr. Tong?

13
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,000
Where did you find him?

14
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,960
<i>At around five in the morning,</i>

15
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:16,680
<i>my villagers and I</i>
<i>were patrolling around the village</i>

16
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:20,360
<i>in case any of your enemies</i>
<i>came into the area.</i>

17
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,400
<i>Then we saw a suspicious car.</i>

18
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,320
Bury him.

19
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,320
Someone's coming. Let's go.

20
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,960
What?

21
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,280
What did they bury here?

22
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:52,480
<i>Luckily, we got him out in time,</i>

23
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,880
<i>so we were able to revive him.</i>

24
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:55,800
Be gentle.

25
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,720
Close it properly.

26
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,480
Chief.

27
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,760
Please make sure he doesn't die.

28
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:05,360
He's an important witness
who can help send that madam to prison.

29
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:07,320
Don't worry. I'll stake my head on it.

30
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,600
- Ready?
- Yes, Chief.

31
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:22,160
Who do you think did it?

32
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:26,000
Who else could it have been
but that madam?

33
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,480
I didn't expect her
to betray him this quickly.

34
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,480
That woman is getting
more ruthless by the day.

35
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,800
That means Jom and Pin are both in danger.

36
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,400
What are you doing? Stealing my things?

37
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,720
No, ma'am. I was cleaning.

38
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,600
Then what's in your hand? Give it to me.

39
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,200
Are you done yet?

40
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,640
Done… Done what?

41
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,800
Cleaning. Are you finished?!
If you are, then get out.

42
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:14,360
Yes, ma'am. I'm done.

43
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,880
Why are all the people around me
so useless? All idiots.

44
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,640
Even my own children are useless.

45
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:25,320
I never wanted you to die, Teera.

46
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,480
If you were still here,

47
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:31,960
you'd have helped me take
Yai's inheritance much faster.

48
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,520
Now wherever I turn,

49
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,840
I have no one left to talk with.

50
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,680
Is there really nothing we can do?

51
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:49,160
Do we really have to wait for the court
to declare Yai a missing person?

52
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,160
It's such a waste of time.

53
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:57,720
Since Paisal didn't leave a will,
the only thing we can do is wait.

54
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,880
But if you're impatient,

55
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:03,480
you could just write a will yourself.

56
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,480
Type it out and forge the signature.

57
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,640
Problem solved.

58
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,480
Isn't that too risky?

59
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,720
It's like gambling.

60
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,720
It's either win or lose.

61
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:18,360
No.

62
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,520
I refuse to lose anything.

63
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,440
I must win.

64
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,000
Thank you, Teera.

65
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,240
I should've listened to you
from the beginning.

66
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:13,520
SIGNATURE: PAISAL

67
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,920
PAISAL THAMRONGRAT
AUTHORIZED SIGNATORY

68
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,160
TESTATOR: PAISAL

69
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,680
- Hey?
- Move it up.

70
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:30,680
- Move it up.
- Urgent sale?

71
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,720
- Is it good now?
- Farm and resort?

72
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,920
That's strange.

73
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
- What is this?
- Hey.

74
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,760
That's the whole farm.

75
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:38,920
Yeah. What's happening?

76
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:42,800
Move aside. What's going on here?

77
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,840
Move aside.

78
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,520
Who put this sign up?

79
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,760
Who ordered this?

80
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,800
Madam has ordered

81
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,440
that starting today,

82
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:57,400
Paisal Farm will shut down.

83
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:00,760
Everyone must pack up and leave

84
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,480
and find new jobs.

85
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,760
- Huh?
- Oh?

86
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:06,120
Why so suddenly?

87
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,440
How can anyone
find a new job this quickly?

88
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,520
- Yeah.
- What are we supposed to do?

89
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,320
Yeah.

90
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,480
URGENT SALE

91
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,800
- Pin.
- What the hell?

92
00:08:14,440 --> 00:08:16,040
- What do we do now?
- Yeah.

93
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,040
How can you do this?

94
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,680
It's like kicking us out.

95
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:22,240
- Right.
- Tear down the sign.

96
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,160
Don't let them sell it.

97
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,320
- Yeah.
- Go ahead.

98
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,920
Get out, you old fart!

99
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,120
Is this real, Auntie?

100
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,520
I'm not dreaming, am I?

101
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,440
I told you before.

102
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,880
Mr. Paisal loved me very much.

103
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:57,080
This farm was always meant to be mine.

104
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:00,240
See? If you obey me,

105
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,160
wealth will pile up in front of you.

106
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,840
Then why didn't Uncle
reveal this will before he died?

107
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:09,080
Why did it suddenly appear now?

108
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,920
That's strange.

109
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:15,200
Nee, if you talk too much,
you won't get a single baht.

110
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,120
Madam.

111
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,960
Are you really going to sell the farm?

112
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:23,120
You're not even the executor
of the estate yet. How can you sell it?

113
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:26,240
Auntie found the will, Pin.

114
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:28,840
Uncle Paisal left
all the inheritance to her alone.

115
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:30,560
There's no need to wait
for the court anymore.

116
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,320
May I see it?

117
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,080
Don't worry.

118
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,640
I'll still give Na his share.

119
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,520
If you marry him,

120
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,840
you'll live comfortably.

121
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,640
Mr. Yai.

122
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:38,840
Dad?

123
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,960
Mr. Yai, we shouldn't stay here long.

124
00:11:57,560 --> 00:11:58,400
Yes.

125
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,920
Is something urgent?

126
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,040
You can't stay here any longer, Pin.

127
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,360
Madam almost killed Mr. Tong.

128
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:08,880
Chief Yam managed to save him,
but now he's in the hospital.

129
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:11,320
You have to come back
to Chief Yam's house with me now.

130
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,000
I still can't go yet.

131
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,480
Madam found the will.

132
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,880
Mr. Paisal left
the entire inheritance to her.

133
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,560
Dad was blinded by her.

134
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,280
It's no surprise
he gave everything to her.

135
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:31,920
I'm not sure if that will is real.

136
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:45,960
Mr. Yai.

137
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:49,440
The will I saw was typed.

138
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:52,200
If your father used his own typewriter,

139
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:56,080
the ribbon should've dried out by now.

140
00:12:56,960 --> 00:13:00,320
But this ink looks like
it was only recently replaced.

141
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:08,480
Wait. I remember now.

142
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,560
Pin.

143
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:19,200
Can you bring me the typewriter
from the cabinet?

144
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:23,560
But will you still have enough strength
in your hands to type, sir?

145
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,240
What do you want to type, Uncle?

146
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,760
I can type it for you.

147
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,520
I can do it.

148
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,320
Can I be alone?

149
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,240
Yes.

150
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:04,320
Pin is sure that my dad typed out
the real will that day.

151
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:09,120
Your dad probably saw
that Pin was Aunt Un's daughter,

152
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,880
so maybe he didn't want her
to see the will.

153
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:18,160
Wait. Then your dad's signature
that Krongsuk has…

154
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,080
A forged signature.

155
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,200
This is bad.

156
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:25,080
We have to find the real will
before that madam does.

157
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:27,920
If we're too late, your whole inheritance
will get blown away in the gambling den.

158
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,600
I don't want my father's things.

159
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,480
All I care about
is how to help Uncle Pload.

160
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:33,400
Yai,

161
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,480
you're still angry at your dad.

162
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,960
But it's all the same thing.

163
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:40,240
The fact that your dad secretly
wrote a will and kept it hidden

164
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:44,080
means he knew what that madam had done.

165
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,320
I just hope Jom had nothing
to do with any of this evil.

166
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,680
Yai.

167
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,320
Why won't you just die already?

168
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:22,920
I hate you. I hate you. I hate you.

169
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:37,640
If good really can overcome evil,

170
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:42,120
please let me find the real will.

171
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:28,720
Here, Uncle.

172
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,800
Mr. Yai will definitely be happy

173
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:41,200
that you made this for him.

174
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:44,760
When he was little,

175
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:47,680
Yai wanted to be a pilot.

176
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:59,160
But it's a pity

177
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:01,320
that I probably…

178
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:07,640
won't be able to give it to him
with my own hands.

179
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,560
No, Uncle.

180
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:13,560
You have to stay

181
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,920
and wait until Mr. Yai comes back.

182
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,040
What are you doing in here?

183
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,680
I came in to clean.

184
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,000
Are you here to pray, Madam?

185
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,640
Pray for what?

186
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,800
What could praying possibly do for me?

187
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:39,680
But you're the one who's going to bless me

188
00:17:40,280 --> 00:17:42,160
by helping me catch Yai.

189
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:47,440
I already told you,
I haven't seen Mr. Yai.

190
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:49,800
Mr. Na already confirmed
he was just mistaken.

191
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:52,280
Stop acting, Pin.

192
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:53,960
I know everything now.

193
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:57,440
Yai is still alive,
and you've been working with him,

194
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:59,000
spying from inside this place.

195
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:09,400
You already killed my mom.

196
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:12,200
Are you really cruel enough
to kill me too?

197
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,760
So you admit it.

198
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,600
The reason I came back

199
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:21,080
was because I wanted to know
how you could be cruel enough

200
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,520
to kill even the person
who loved you with all her heart.

201
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:28,720
Because there was someone
I loved more than Un.

202
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,880
I had no choice but to choose.

203
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:35,240
You're the same. If Na didn't want you,

204
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:38,040
I wouldn't keep you either.

205
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,360
How many people
have you killed for Mr. Na?

206
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:45,680
And do you really think he'd be happy
having a murderer for a mother?

207
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:47,920
You know too much now!

208
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:50,960
If you weren't someone
Na was hopelessly in love with,

209
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:53,800
you wouldn't even have
the chance to stand here talking.

210
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:56,080
I'm giving you one last chance.

211
00:18:56,680 --> 00:18:58,600
Come over to my side.

212
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:00,640
Be a good daughter-in-law.

213
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,480
Help get rid of Mr. Yai,

214
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:05,000
and you'll get your share.

215
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:07,600
How much?

216
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,360
You don't get to choose.

217
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:13,280
You wouldn't dare to kill me.

218
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:18,120
If I die, Mr. Na will hate you
for the rest of his life.

219
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:20,880
Then I'll just slash your face instead.

220
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,760
- Pin.
- Jom.

221
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,880
Jom, Madam was going to kill me.

222
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,720
Stop working for her already.

223
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:32,240
I was only threatening her.

224
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:33,640
Don't let her get away.

225
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:35,920
She's the only one who can lead us to Yai.

226
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:39,960
So it was you who told her?

227
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:43,120
I'm not going to keep being a fool
and letting you deceive me anymore.

228
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:44,120
Come here.

229
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:54,280
Let go of me.

230
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:09,080
Na.

231
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,120
Na. Na.

232
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,640
Nee.

233
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,080
Go get Pin for me.

234
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,240
Tell her I'm not feeling well.

235
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:25,120
Na, stop pretending already.

236
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,600
Go help Pin now.

237
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,240
What happened to her?

238
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:32,840
Auntie took her
and locked her up at the resort.

239
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,880
I'm scared she's going to kill her.

240
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,160
What are you talking about?

241
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,320
Killing people is against the law.

242
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,960
How could she kill anyone she wants?

243
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,960
Auntie is a murderer.

244
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:47,880
She killed Uncle Paisal, Aunt Un,
and anyone who gets in her way.

245
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:49,960
Auntie has never killed anyone.

246
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:53,440
Na, stop lying to yourself already.

247
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:55,720
You're not doing it for Auntie.

248
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,720
You're doing it
so you yourself can feel better.

249
00:20:58,640 --> 00:20:59,840
You already know the truth.

250
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:03,320
You even saw Mr. Tong
being dragged off to be killed.

251
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,280
Na,

252
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:07,720
stop pretending like nothing happened.

253
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:09,440
But Auntie is our mother, Nee.

254
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,320
But the person you call Mother

255
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:15,600
is about to kill Pin.

256
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,640
How could she kill Pin

257
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:22,200
when she just told me she was going
to arrange my wedding to her?

258
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,600
How can you marry her?

259
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:26,080
Pin is still married to Mr. Yai.

260
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:28,160
- Their marriage is there--
- I don't care!

261
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,720
All I know is that I have
to marry Pin as soon as possible.

262
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,520
Regardless of whether Yai
is dead or alive,

263
00:21:35,280 --> 00:21:37,120
I have to make Pin mine.

264
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:44,880
In three days,

265
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:48,680
I'll pay compensation to all of your
according to the labor law,

266
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:51,760
along with an extra payment
as a sign of goodwill.

267
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:54,520
I apologize
for how violently my people acted.

268
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:56,160
It was all a misunderstanding.

269
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:59,280
Besides,

270
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:02,000
everyone here is like family to me,

271
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:05,080
so I would like to invite all of you

272
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:07,600
to be witnesses

273
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:11,720
to my nephew Na's
auspicious ceremony tomorrow.

274
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,400
An auspicious ceremony?

275
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,520
Is tomorrow Mr. Na's birthday?

276
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,280
Even more auspicious than that.

277
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:23,560
It's Tatsana and Pinanong's wedding.

278
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:26,560
What?

279
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:28,280
How is that even possible?

280
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:30,880
So, Pin…

281
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:38,520
Mr. Na told me to bring food for Pin.

282
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:40,800
Open it first.

283
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,560
Hey.

284
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:46,240
‪Here.

285
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:47,800
Give it to me.

286
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:45,640
<i>Madam is going to force you</i>
<i>to marry Mr. Na tomorrow.</i>

287
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:48,120
<i>Piak can't get out to tell Mr. Yai</i>

288
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:50,640
<i>because Madam's people</i>
<i>have been keeping a tight watch over him.</i>

289
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:55,440
<i>But luckily, someone kind-hearted</i>
<i>happened to come help us.</i>

290
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:28,160
Yai is here. Gather everyone now.

291
00:25:28,240 --> 00:25:29,080
Hurry!

292
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,440
Hey.

293
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:42,240
Yai is here. Let's go.

294
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:37,240
Yai!

295
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,480
You lured my people into chasing you

296
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:07,520
so Piak and Waan

297
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:09,760
could escape
and go tell Mr. Yai, didn't you?

298
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:13,400
Pin saved my life once.

299
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:15,400
She's my only friend.

300
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:18,560
Auntie, please let her go.

301
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:20,320
She may be your friend,

302
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:22,000
but I'm your mother.

303
00:27:22,080 --> 00:27:25,360
A mother who forbids her child
from calling her Mother

304
00:27:25,440 --> 00:27:27,160
doesn't count as a mother.

305
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:29,240
- You ungrateful child!
- Go ahead!

306
00:27:45,160 --> 00:27:46,800
That's more like it.

307
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:49,040
That's what it means to be my daughter.

308
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:52,280
Go on. Slap me.

309
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,680
Slap me right here.

310
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:56,160
If you dare slap your own mother,

311
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:58,160
then I won't have to worry
about you anymore.

312
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,240
You'll be strong.

313
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:02,560
No one will ever be able
to bully you again, just like me.

314
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:04,320
Go on. Slap me.

315
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:06,160
Slap me! Slap me!

316
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,120
Slap me!

317
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,320
- Slap me!
- No!

318
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:14,080
No. I won't be like you.

319
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,960
I don't want to be like you.

320
00:28:17,040 --> 00:28:18,600
I will never be like you!

321
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,440
Coward!

322
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:25,840
You're a coward!

323
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:30,040
Auntie!

324
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:32,720
Auntie, please stop doing evil.

325
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:40,800
I'll bow to your feet. I'm begging you.

326
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,440
Please.

327
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:12,600
Auntie!

328
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:17,160
- I'm going to help Pin.
- Hey, hey.

329
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:20,800
Be careful.
This could be a trap to lure you in.

330
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:22,760
That's very possible.

331
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:25,040
It would best to plan carefully first.

332
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,040
Otherwise, both you and Pin
will be in danger.

333
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:28,720
I agree.

334
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:32,080
If you're still stubborn,
don't say I didn't warn you.

335
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:38,720
Fine. Whatever the majority says.

336
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:40,120
I'm just the vocal minority here.

337
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:50,400
You two probably can't go back now.

338
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,080
Stay here tonight.

339
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,200
They can stay in my room.

340
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:58,600
I'll sleep in Phong's room.

341
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:05,920
Phong, keep an eye on Yai.

342
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,320
I don't trust what he said.

343
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:09,880
Yes, sir.

344
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,920
I know what you're thinking.

345
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:33,320
Don't even think about sneaking off
to save Pin by yourself.

346
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:38,240
My wife is about to marry another man,

347
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:40,640
and you expect me to do nothing?

348
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:42,200
Or do you not worry about your lover?

349
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:48,880
What lover? Don't talk nonsense.

350
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:51,280
I'm not blind.

351
00:30:51,360 --> 00:30:53,480
I can see how you feel about Tatsanee.

352
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:57,040
Fine. But if you're going to save her,

353
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:59,280
you need to know
the situation first, don't you?

354
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:03,000
They might've already
moved Pin somewhere else.

355
00:31:03,080 --> 00:31:05,480
If you just charge in,
you'll only get yourself killed.

356
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:13,080
There's one person
who can help us find out.

357
00:31:13,160 --> 00:31:15,520
Who now? Noi?

358
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:17,320
By now, she's probably
been locked away and forgotten too.

359
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:23,520
Or you mean…

360
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:45,440
You can't go in.

361
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,880
I'm from Livestock Services.

362
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,640
I came to vaccinate the animals.

363
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:51,480
No orders were given. You can't go in.

364
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:52,800
You'd better turn the car around.

365
00:31:53,920 --> 00:31:57,080
But I'm friends with Jom,
the head worker here.

366
00:31:57,160 --> 00:31:58,400
Go get Jom for me.

367
00:31:58,480 --> 00:32:00,080
I told you that you can't go in.

368
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,120
Don't you understand?

369
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:10,600
Jin.

370
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,000
You should go back, Jin.

371
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:24,000
I want to see Pin.

372
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:25,760
I want to know if she's safe.

373
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:29,920
I'm here. No one is going to hurt Pin.

374
00:32:30,520 --> 00:32:31,640
You don't need to worry.

375
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:33,800
Then why can't I see her?

376
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,760
Tell me where she is.

377
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,440
Aunt Un's house?

378
00:32:38,520 --> 00:32:40,360
The main house? Or the resort?

379
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:46,000
If you won't tell me,
then I'll go find her myself.

380
00:32:46,760 --> 00:32:48,000
Yai is still alive.

381
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,360
Madam wants to get revenge for Aunt Un.

382
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:55,560
I just want to help her catch Yai
and hand him over to the police.

383
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:58,120
Don't use that as an excuse.

384
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:01,760
You know very well how evil Madam is,

385
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:05,240
but you still shut your eyes
and help her because you're selfish.

386
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,080
You just want to end up with Pin.

387
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:15,160
If you won't tell me where Pin is,
don't call yourself my friend anymore.

388
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:22,200
That's up to you, Jin.

389
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:46,320
Pin got locked up?

390
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:51,000
That madam is going to force Pin
to marry Na tomorrow.

391
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,760
So I came to beg you to help us find out

392
00:33:54,320 --> 00:33:56,080
whether Pin
is still being held at the resort.

393
00:33:57,080 --> 00:34:00,880
If my friend gets hurt because of Mr. Yai,
I'll never forgive him.

394
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:04,560
You know Yai is still alive?

395
00:34:04,640 --> 00:34:07,920
When I went to visit Uncle Win,
Pin told me everything.

396
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:10,400
I think Pin was moved to the main house,

397
00:35:11,120 --> 00:35:13,320
because it's being heavily guarded.

398
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:17,560
As for the front of the farm, every
vehicle going in and out is being checked.

399
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:20,160
It won't be easy
to get in there and help her.

400
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:24,640
They'll definitely hold the wedding
at the main house.

401
00:35:25,640 --> 00:35:27,800
Shouldn't we report this to the police?

402
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,560
Pin isn't willing to marry him.

403
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:32,640
She's being unlawfully confined.

404
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:34,800
The police have every right
to go in and rescue her.

405
00:35:36,080 --> 00:35:37,560
I agree with Ms. Jin.

406
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:41,360
If you don't want to turn yourself in,
Ms. Jin can file a report

407
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:44,160
because she's Pin's close friend.

408
00:35:51,080 --> 00:35:53,400
No. I'll turn myself in.

409
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:55,720
I'll end everything myself.

410
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:00,960
I'll contact my law professor right away,

411
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:03,840
and tomorrow, we'll go to the station.

412
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:27,920
Pin.

413
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:32,200
I went into town
and rented a wedding dress for you.

414
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:36,080
Try it on and see if it fits.

415
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:46,640
Are you really sure

416
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,800
you want to marry someone
who doesn't love you at all?

417
00:36:57,600 --> 00:36:59,240
When you came back to the farm,

418
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,680
weren't you the one who told Auntie

419
00:37:03,920 --> 00:37:05,320
you wanted to marry me?

420
00:37:09,360 --> 00:37:11,000
I was only lying to her.

421
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:15,600
You already know

422
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,440
- that Mr. Yaiis still alive--
- Enough, Pin.

423
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,960
I don't want to know anything.

424
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:23,440
Well…

425
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:26,720
I'll be good to you.

426
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,200
Whatever Yai did for you,

427
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:33,680
I'll do it too. I'll do it even better.

428
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:36,200
I only need you

429
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:38,880
to love me a little.

430
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:46,480
How could I ever love a man
who abandoned his own fiancée?

431
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,880
You're going to marry me,

432
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:54,960
even though you caused Ms. On
unbearable pain?

433
00:37:58,640 --> 00:38:00,040
Just thinking about the day

434
00:38:00,120 --> 00:38:03,520
she had to run for her life
back to Bangkok,

435
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:06,320
I already feel heartbroken for her.

436
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:12,160
And yet you still want to marry me.

437
00:38:14,240 --> 00:38:16,480
Do you really feel nothing at all?

438
00:40:22,640 --> 00:40:27,760
I LOVE YOU, AND I ALWAYS WILL
ON

439
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:34,480
<i>Na, do you remember?</i>

440
00:40:35,840 --> 00:40:37,680
<i>Back when we were overseas,</i>

441
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:41,040
<i>you wanted this watch.</i>

442
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:46,800
<i>I promised when I arrived in Thailand,</i>
<i>I'd buy it for you.</i>

443
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:50,640
<i>But terrible things happened to us first.</i>

444
00:40:55,120 --> 00:40:57,160
<i>I wanted to keep that promise,</i>

445
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:59,720
<i>but it was so expensive.</i>

446
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:02,480
<i>I couldn't afford to buy it for you</i>

447
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:06,360
<i>unless I sold my engagement ring.</i>

448
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:21,280
<i>I never regretted it for even a second</i>

449
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:25,360
<i>if it would make you happy and bring us</i>
<i>back to the way we used to be.</i>

450
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:29,000
<i>I love you,</i>

451
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:32,720
<i>and I always will.</i>

452
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:38,400
I LOVE YOU, AND I ALWAYS WILL
ON

453
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:36,000
NA

454
00:42:42,440 --> 00:42:44,800
<i>On. It's me.</i>

455
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:47,240
What do you want now?

456
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:49,560
I…

457
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:55,080
I just wanted to ask

458
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:58,600
how On is doing.

459
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:01,120
My daughter is still alive.

460
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:03,160
But my grandchild…

461
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:07,240
the one in On's womb

462
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:12,240
never got the chance to see the world
because of its father's selfishness.

463
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:16,480
Father?

464
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:25,480
On was pregnant?

465
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:32,360
On had a miscarriage because of you.

466
00:43:33,600 --> 00:43:36,640
You killed your own child, you bastard.

467
00:44:54,480 --> 00:44:55,560
So brave.

468
00:44:55,640 --> 00:44:57,240
That's Bandit Yai's wife.

469
00:44:57,320 --> 00:45:01,240
If you want Pinanong to be your wife,
you have to kill him with your own hands.

470
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:02,760
I'll give him to you.

471
00:45:07,800 --> 00:45:10,800
<i>This is the last thing</i>
<i>I can do for you, Pin.</i>

472
00:45:10,880 --> 00:45:13,200
I want to see your face one last time

473
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:15,560
before I lose the chance
to ever see you again.

474
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:17,640
You'll be okay. We have to stay together.

475
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:19,880
Pin. Pin.

476
00:45:59,360 --> 00:46:02,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
